author: Natasha Nabila
text:
Contacted the club to cancel my membership and was told to reach out to someone who‚Äôs ‚Äúbest at it.‚Äù I was informed I needed to clear my outstanding payment then can cancel even though the payment was unintentionally unsuccessful, took initiative to pay manually and there had already been auto-deducted for that same month. So essentially, I was charged twice in one month. And was told that there will be reimbursement for the late payment fee. ( apparently, reimbursement takes 3 months, so your membership has to continue for 4 months if you‚Äôd like to be reimbursed.) Smart yeah? So got to pay extra 4 months just to get reimbursement LOL.

After transferring the payment and updating the staff in August, NO REPLY. Then in October, I was charged again. When I followed up, I was told that ‚Äúit has always been on the member to make sure they have confirmation‚Äù  basically blaming me for their team‚Äôs lack of follow-up.

Explained that it‚Äôs unreasonable to say it‚Äôs the member‚Äôs job to follow up with themselves when the staff clearly said I could cancel after clearing my payments. Which i did, but again to NO REPLY. (Purposely eh? So got to pay extra months? Lol) I followed every instruction given, the lack of confirmation and poor communication shouldn‚Äôt fall on me. Yet instead of taking responsibility for NOT REPLYING, I kept getting the same copy-paste response: ‚Äú it will be seen as your fault for not confirming‚Äù

Now I‚Äôm told I still need to pay another month under the ‚ÄúX+1‚Äù policy on top of the two extra months already deducted because of their staff‚Äôs failure to reply. This could‚Äôve been done in August when it wasn't my fault that staff DID NOT reply me. When I showed other members had the same experience, the response was just a thumbs-up!

This is completely unacceptable and unprofessional. If refunds aren‚Äôt allowed, the least you could do is resolve the issue instead of BLAMING your customers and making them pay extra for your team‚Äôs mistake. Be a better manager, your customers deserve accountability, not excuses.

Unfortunately (or intentionally), my payment deduction is on the 30th of the month. On 30 Sep, my bank was charged. AF explained to me that my membership ends in Oct.

author: Brian Chong
text:
My dad was a customer of this gym and his experience with it was horrendous.

He notified the staff via WhatsApp in April, a month before the end of his contract, that he planned to discontinue it. However, the staff ignored the message and only read it on May, to which she replied that the gym would not be opened because of covid so he will not be able to cancel his contract during this period.

Without any follow up from the staff, the gym  charged his card for the subsequent months during covid because they have an auto renewal subscription system stated in their contract. How lovely.

When he realised this in August, he called the staff and she told him that he should know how to cancel the contract on his own and to ask my siblings how they cancelled theirs. (They also had bad experiences and cancelled their plans)

When asked why she did not follow up with my dad on the cancellation after several months of ghosting his message, her reply was that it was "administratively impossible" for the staff to do so due to shortage of staff. Apparently, customers should be the ones to follow up with the cancellation after the gym reopens, not the staff.

First of all, why is shortage of staff in your gym a problem that your customers should care about? Shortage of manpower is not a valid excuse to provide substandard customer service.

Second, why are the customers responsible to follow up themselves after they informed the staff about cancellation? Isn't this the job of the gym staff?

In addition, a free month of membership after 12 months which was promised by the staff during his registration was not even honored.

I just want to say how appalled I am at the level of incompetance displayed by the staff, who failed to accomplish even the most basic things like replying to WhatApp messages on time and following up on requests made by customers, constantly creating excuses for their inadequate quality of service.

If you are considering becoming a member of this gym, I highly advise you rethink and stay away.

Lights are constantly flickering, slow to fix. Same vibes as lifting in an abandoned basement with 1 light.

[Edit]
Since leaving the review, the gym has fixed the lights (within 1 week) and the music is now softer.

Originally 1 star, I upped to 3 stars, because they seemed sincere in how the gym is perceived, and seem to want to rectify issues with the gym properly. Props to them!

text:
Gym is very small, and it can get very cramped during peak hours. Got banned from the gym for visiting their gym more than my home gym, and refusing to transfer my membership over.

Update (July 2021) - Takes them quite long to replace/fix equipment. Customer service leaves a lot to be desired; Don't expect much from business ran by a small franchise owner, tons of inflexibility that is apparent.

Update (Dec 2021) - For anyone cancelling their membership, do it BEFORE the last month in your contract. This joke of a gym counts the NEXT calendar month as your last month. I applied to cancel my membership in early Nov, and ended up with my last day on 31 Dec.

My contract was supposed to end this month, as I signed up for a 1.5 year contract starting Jan 2020. The gym refuses to let me terminate my contract stating that "Contract is auto extended by the period its frozen".

The gym has closed for several months due to government regulations, but that does not mean that they can just unilaterally extend my contract for a few months.

Potential newcomers that got enticed by their recent promotion, think twice before signing with this gym. The AF at Northpoint City is at least three times bigger with more equipment and better customer service IMO.
